# Vendored third-party assets must NOT be line-ending-normalized: they are minified
# bundles, and any CRLF rewrite (a) bloats them and (b) — critically — changes their
# bytes so the Subresource-Integrity hash in index.html no longer matches and the browser
# refuses to load the script. Keep them exactly as fetched from the CDN. (audit T10, 2026-06-14)
vendor/** -text
